text: I'm gonna be blunt.  This is only a teaser, but I'm already not that confident in this movie. The book, in my opinion, was mediocre, and from what i can tell, this movie is doing a lot of things different, which isn't necessarily bad, but is very odd.  Since when are the Sixers (sux0rs, whatever) NASCAR drivers? There was never a giant car chase scene in the books.  Since when has there ever been an orc? There was no such character in the books.  Where's Art3mis, not even a single mention of her (not that I care, the romance in the books was kinda bad, imo).  This is most likely going to make money, seeing as it's a Spielberg movie, but I doubt it's going to be a good movie.

text: I think this is going to be another misfire for Spielberg quite frankly. it has an odd concept that usually doesn't do well in movies, ie the "in the video game" concept. people play video games everyday. so the thought of watching a movie about others doing so I don't think it going to bring in the big numbers. plus VR game technology is struggling due to lack of interest.  I think had he went with one of the films he optioned but put on the back burner:"Robopocalypse" a horror/sci-fi movie about killer cyborgs, it would have been a better pick for a great summer blockbuster. but this, its not enough to dazzle with CGI anymore.

text: Other 1980's pop culture icons that I hope appear in *Ready* *Player* *One* are:  *Ghostbusters* The Kitt car from *Knight* *Rider*  *Max* *Headroom* from those Pepsi TV ads *ED*-*207* from RoboCop *Pac*-*Man* & *Space* *Invaders* from the coin-operated arcade games (which were featured in the book)  The *Rubik's* *Cube* (even though that is probably one of the most *overused* props in movie history) Michael Jackson's *Thriller* album Mario from *Super* *Mario* *Bros.* *Gorbachev's* *top-of-his-head* *birthmark* and the *Energizer* *Bunny* (It just keeps going and going and...)  Anyway, I know I'm being silly, but there's nothing wrong with letting one's imagination run wild from time to time.

text: Okay, This is one of my favorite books and most anticipated movies ever. I have watched the trailer more than a few times. I think I watched all the reactions and have watched and read everything I can find on the release. Here are a few things I have been able to figure out and a few corrections for people. (possible spoilers)  1. The Stacks look like anyone who read the book would have thought of it but the Stacks where in Oklahoma city in the book and he did not make it Columbus until after the first key is found. His hide out in the van is very accurate to the book also.   2. As Wade enters the oasis they show a scene of Og's birthday party. Many of the Easter eggs here have been covered.   3. The scene with the Iron Giant is 3 people in the book but everyone seems to get this part wrong. E.Cline confirmed on E that it was Diato, Shoto and Parzival. They also said the Iron Giant plays a larger role in the movie that I have two ideas because of some tribute to The iron Giant movie, this could be Diato. I could be wrong but that is my speculation.   3. The Delorien spinning out looked like the Planet he went to school on in my mind. This would be highly out of place because Wade did not have a car in the game until he had the cash to get some of the add ons in the game from sponsorship.   4. The scorpion and Joist part is strange. At first I thought it might be part of the end battle but I am starting to think they fully changed the first key challenge. This is 2045 after all and in VR. It would be a little weird to watch a kid playing a coin operated video game while a Lich watches him.   4. As the trailer moves to the Race scene, There is no race in the book and this is an adaptation that I am excited to see. Those of you who think it will be a clear recreation of the book are wrong. I would hate going to see this movie if that is all that it was. I fully expect to see the changes like Irok (TJ Miller) playing a very different and much more expanded role. There is no way to pack the whole story even into a 3 hour movie and as everyone says the books are always better than the movie.   5. The last parts I would point out is that we do see Artimas. She is riding Kenadas bike from Akira (ITS NOT A TRON LIGHT CYCLE). We also get to See Aech who is driving the truck. There is also a Scan code on one of the IOI cars that takes you to a IOI recruitment webpage.   6. There is one small Easter egg in the trailer that I am not seeing anyone talking about but I noticed one thing towards the end and very hard to catch. When Wade rips off his visor, you can see Nolan Sorento in the reflection. A few people noticed this but I think they missed it and it is not a reflection. I know I dropped a spoiler warning on my predictions but I do not want to drop this spoiler. What I will say is that I believe this is not a reflection but a delay from his visor and the look on Wades face and the fact that he is in his hide out can only be from one spot in the book. It is right after he logs out from his first meeting with Nolan and something big just happened. I highly doubt this is him being surprised after finding the first clue as others have suggested.   ¬†I would add that those not in the know should get a better feel from a longer trailer and I highly suspect the full trailer and not the teaser is going to have Halidays message in there and a more in depth look at the story line than the teaser. Those are my thoughts. Let me know if you guys think I am off on anything and sorry for the spelling and grammar errors.

text: Okay, so lemme tell yall a story.  Yesterday, I walked into class, sat down at my desk, and pulled out Ready Player One. I had already read the book, and was rereading it just because I love the book. SO this kid who sits in front of me goes, " Where'd ya get that book?" and I simply replied " My house. " He replies with, " I've been wanting to read it for a while, so I can watch the movie when it releases." And I didn't respond, because I had no clue of movie was gonna be made, so I was super skeptical. Then, today, I'm eating dinner, and my book is set up on the table. My uncle, who's been staying with us the past few days, says, " Who's reading Ready Player One?" I tell him that I am, and he also mentions the movie. SO I just went up and checked it out online, and it exists.  I don't care if the movie ends up like garbage, my ass in gonna be in that movie theater seat.
